Erste Heads for Longest Losing Streak in Three Months on Outlook

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-02-25T09:14:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/erste-heads-for-longest-losing-streak-in-three-months-on-outlook.html
  Erste Group Bank AG  fell for a third
day in Czech trading, heading for its longest streak of declines
since November, after the Austrian lender said taxes and its
Hungarian and Romanian units will cap earnings.  The stock fell as much as 1.6 percent and traded down 1.1
percent at 921 koruna as of 10:05 a.m. in  Prague , heading for
its lowest close since Feb. 14. In Vienna, its home market,
Erste retreated 1.1 percent to 37.565 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  